CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1949, pg. 4 reads: "World Fellowship - A few representatives participating in World Fellowship United Nations festival to be held at the Centre Avenue branch YWCA, are shown above. In the front row, left to right, are: Miss Arrie Moore, Brazil; Mrs. Nathan Brown, China; Miss Marie Mellon, Japan; Mrs. Leola Bonick, Egypt.  Back row: Mrs. Alfred Rector, Holland; Mrs. W.S. Africa, and Mrs. Harvey Hatcher, Africa. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Participants in World Fellowship United Nations Festival, front row from left: Arrie Moore, Mrs. Nathan Brown, Marie Mellon, Leola Bonick; back row: Mrs. Alfred Rector, Mrs. W.S. Africa, and Mrs. Harvey Hatcher, posed possibly in YWCA
